        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 3:41AM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 341 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Ludlow, or 12 miles south of Bowman, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Scranton, Gascoyne, and Bowman Haley Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
